{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772563567,"nonce":"DBUXsTJzmyGSe3BvKAy+MPlTBfg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vgOqH","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/340","origin":"github"},"title":"Add missing dev tools to workspace bootstrap","message":"## Summary\n\nThe workspace dev setup should install all anticipated development tools so that\nagents and contributors have a complete environment out of the box, without needing\nto install packages ad-hoc during work.\n\n## Context\n\nWhile working on linter fixes for `marine_ais_tools`, an agent attempted to\n`pip install autopep8` into the system Python — which is blocked by PEP 668 and\nwould have been unsafe regardless. The tool is available via apt (`python3-autopep8`)\nand could also be installed into the workspace `.venv`, but neither was set up.\n\nThis revealed that the workspace bootstrap doesn't install several common dev tools\nthat agents routinely need.\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### Add missing dev tools to workspace setup\n\nThe following tools should be available after running the workspace dev setup:\n\n**Via apt (system prerequisites):**\n- `python3-autopep8` — PEP 8 auto-formatter\n- `python3-isort` — import sorting (already installed)\n- `pipx` — isolated CLI tool installation\n\n**Via `.venv` (installed during dev setup):**\n- Any tools not available via apt that are needed for development workflows\n\n### Update documentation\n\n- Document which dev tools are available and how they were installed\n- Reference the Python package management ADR (see #339) for the policy\n\n## Depends On\n\n- #339 (ADR: Python package management policy) — establishes the rules for where\n  tools get installed\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}